ashire, England, United Kingdom":"Bold, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Agnes","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized version of the Greek name <i>Hagnē</i>, from the feminine form of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes was born in 1200, in Bold, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Matthew de Bold. She died in 1290, in her hometown, at the age of 90."},"et":{"1200–1290":"1200–1290","1190–1242":"1190–1242","1220–1323":"1220–1323","1225–1312":"1225–1312","1190":"1190","1225":"1225","1312":"1312","1323":"1323","1200":"1200","1220":"1220","1242":"1242","1290":"1290","Bold, Lancashire, England":"Bold, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Prescot, Lancashire, England":"Prescot, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bold, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Bold, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1200–1290":"1200–1290","1190–1242":"1190–1242","1220–1323":"1220–1323","1225–1312":"1225–1312","1190":"1190","1225":"1225","1312":"1312","1323":"1323","1200":"1200","1220":"1220","1242":"1242","1290":"1290","Bold, Lancashire, England":"Bold, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Prescot, Lancashire, England":"Prescot, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningask